<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFA7BA0BBC33FB30BB08F2C1" pageId="27" pageNumber="646" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFA7BA0BBC33FB30BB08F2C1" blockId="27.[2080,2674,3038,3462]" pageId="27" pageNumber="646">
The species forms a complex with 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA7BA0BBE17FB30BA61F357" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="649" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pumilus">C. pumilus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA7BA0BBC74FB18BB0CF357" box="[2150,2346,3192,3225]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="646" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atsinanana">C. atsinanana</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFA7BA0BBD81FB18B800F357" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" box="[2451,2598,3192,3225]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="646" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">C. pusillus</taxonomicName>
that stretches across south-western Arabia, Africa, 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFA7BA0BBC74FBA7BB2CF326" box="[2150,2314,3271,3304]" name="Madagascar" pageId="27" pageNumber="646">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, and other Indian Ocean islands. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
